SubClassOf(obo:OBI_0000835 ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:RO_0000087 obo:OBI_0000571))

# Class: obo:OBI_0001930 (categorical value specification)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 obo:OBI_0001930 "A value specification that is specifies one category out of a fixed number of nominal categories"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label obo:OBI_0001930 "categorical value specification")
SubClassOf(obo:OBI_0001930 obo:OBI_0001933)

# Class: obo:OBI_0001933 (value specification)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 obo:OBI_0001933 "An information content entity that specifies a value within a classification scheme or on a quantitative scale."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label obo:OBI_0001933 "value specification")
SubClassOf(obo:OBI_0001933 obo:IAO_0000030)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> (Material)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> "Instances of Portions Of Matter whose shape is relevant for their dispostion to participate in a manufacturing process may be (subclasses of) objects that bear a 'blank role' in the context of the manufacturing process."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> "Material is defined in terms of the three main perspectives that material specifications rely on: the structure of the material (\"intensive quality\"), the performance of the material (\"behavoiral material property\") and the processing the material must have undergone (\"output of some process\").

When defining specific materials/material taxonomies, these three aspects shall be taken into account in the aristotelian (\"per genus et differentiam\") as differentiation."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> "The sum of portions of matter of the same type form a portion of matter of that type."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> "Material"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> "material"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> "Portion of Material"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> "A Material is a Portion Of Matter that may participate in some Manifacturing Process and whose shape is not relevant for its participation in the Manifacuring Process."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:RO_0000053 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005>) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:RO_0000086 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:RO_0002353 obo:BFO_0000015)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001> (portion of matter)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001> "It is also representing a distinct physical or conceptual part of a material or substance.

The open energy ontology OEO defines portion of matter as a subclass of object aggregate, which implies countability. Our portion is not (precisely) countable and thus bearer of intensive properties."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001> "Lome explanation for portion of matter: \"What is a molecule cluster at the cellular level? Contrary to the molecular level, at the cellular level of granularity the boundary of each molecule is outside of the level of granular focus. What forms a discontinuous cluster of countable individual molecules and thus bona fide objects at the molecular level, is a continuous and non-countable molecular substance at coarser levels of
granularity. At these coarser levels, the individual molecules cannot be differentiated and demarcated anymore and the cluster as a whole possesses only fiat inner boundaries.\""@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001> "portion of matter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001> "A material entity that is not demarcated by any physical discontinuities. At some finer level of granularity it is an object aggregate, at some coarser level of granularity it is a fiat object part,but at this level of granularity it is neither."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001> obo:BFO_0000040)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000002> (engineered material)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000002> "We recognize that some of the materials in the subclasses also occur naturally. However, these are not within the scope of our consideration for technical use."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000002> "engineered material"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000002> "An Engineered Material is a Material that is output of a Manufacturing Process."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000002> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005> (behavioral material property)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005> "Technical materials are complex object aggregates. The properties that are determined for those object aggregates are intrinsically associated with the methodologies employed in the measurement process. This is in contrast to typical 'physical' properties, which like e.g. mass that can be determined to high accuracy independently of the measurement process. 
As a consequence, the behavoiral material properties in the ontology are differeciated according to their measurement method, e.g. Brinell hardness and Vickers hardness are different types of indentation hardness rather than different measures/quantification (GDC) of the materials property 'indentation hardness'.
 The 'unit idenifieres' of such properties (e.g. \"HV1\", \"HV10\", \"HBW\") are strictly speaking not units but rather references to the measurement methodology used to determine a numeric value that quantifies the property."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005> "behavioral material property"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005> "A property is a material trait in terms of the kind and magnitude of response to a specific imposed stimulus. Generally, definitions of properties are made independent of material shape and size.

(Callister, W.D., Rethwisch, D.G., Materials Science and Engineering, Wiley, 2014)

We only deal with intensive (system-size independent) materrial properties. Extensive properties that depend on the testpiece/specimen/probe size should be found in the respective testing method modules."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005> obo:BFO_0000017)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:BFO_0000054 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000950>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:RO_0000052 ObjectIntersectionOf(obo:BFO_0000040 ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:RO_0000056 obo:BFO_0000015))))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008> (process attribute)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008> "Process attribute for a process has a similar application to specifically dependened continuant (SDC) for an independent continuant (IC). Furthermore, process attribute describes how SDCs of some participants, i.e., ICs, change in a process. 

Specific rates, e.g., tensile rate, cooling rate, etc. should be added as  subclasses of this class."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008> "process attribute"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008> "process characteristic"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008> "a process attribute is a dependent occurrent that existentially depends on a process."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008> "Tensile rate in a tensile testing process. Cooling rate in a quenching process"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008> obo:BFO_0000003)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000075> (mold device)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000075> "mold device"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000075> "A form used to cast an object of a desired shape."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000075> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000503> (ASTM grainsize)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000503> "ASTM grainsize"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000503> "The ASTM grain size is a scalar specifically describing the size of grains in a crystalline material as defined by ASTM standards."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000503> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> (aggregate state)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> "aggregate state"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> "The aggregate state is a morphological quality representing the physical state of a material, such as solid, liquid, or gas."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> ObjectExactCardinality(1 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000519> (application of electric field)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000519> "application of electric field"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000519> "An application of (an) electric field is the process of subjecting a material to an electric field to observe its behavior or modify its properties."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000519> obo:BFO_0000015)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000520> (application of heat flux)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000520> "application of heat flux"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000520> "An application of heat flux describes the process of transferring thermal energy to or from a material, often used in thermal property measurements."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000520> obo:BFO_0000015)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000521> (application of magnetic field)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000521> "application of magnetic field"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000521> "An application of (a) magnetic field is the process of subjecting a material to a magnetic field to study its magnetic properties or induce magnetization."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000521> obo:BFO_0000015)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000522> (application of mechanical load)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000522> "application of mechanical load"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000522> "An application of mechanical load is the process of applying force or stress to a material to observe its response or measure its properties."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000522> obo:BFO_0000015)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000523> (application of substance)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000523> "application of substance"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000523> "The application of (a) substance is the process of applying a material or substance to a surface or within a system."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000523> obo:BFO_0000015)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000538> (bulk)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000538> "bulk"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000538> "The bulk is a fiat object part that describes the volume or mass of material considered as a whole, often in contrast to surface or interface phenomena."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000538> obo:BFO_0000024)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000538> ObjectAllValuesFrom(obo:BFO_0000050 ObjectUnionOf(obo:BFO_0000027 obo:BFO_0000030)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000549> (change of temperature)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000549> "change of temperature"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000549> "A change of temperature is a process describing the variation in thermal energy within a material or system over time or due to external influences."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000549> obo:BFO_0000015)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000577> (composite material)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000577> "composite material"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000577> "A Composite Material is an Engineered Material that 'consists of' some Material that has a Matrix role and of some Material that has a Filler role."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000577> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000002> ObjectIntersectionOf(ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:BFO_0000051 ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000002> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:RO_0000087 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000845>))) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:BFO_0000051 ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000002> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:RO_0000087 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020001>))))))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> (Datenverarbeitung)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> "Datenverarbeitung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> "Rechenprozess"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> "computing process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> "A process that involves the systematic use of computational methods and tools to perform simulations, analyses, or data transformations to achieve specific scientific or engineering goals."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> "Ein Prozess, der die systematische Verwendung von rechnerischen Methoden und Werkzeugen umfasst, um Simulationen, Analysen oder Datenumwandlungen durchzuführen, um spezifische wissenschaftliche oder technische Ziele zu erreichen."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> obo:OBI_0000011)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> ObjectIntersectionOf(ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:OBI_0000293 obo:IAO_0000030) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:OBI_0000299 obo:IAO_0000030)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> (crystal structure)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> "crystal structure"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> "The crystal structure is a morphologic quality that describes the periodic geometric arrangement of entities in a crystalline material. The finite set of periodic geometric arrangements is described by the 14 possible Bravais Lattices in three-dimensional space."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> ObjectExactCardinality(1 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000595> (defect density)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000595> "defect density"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000595> "The defect density is a morphological quality describing the number of defects per unit volume or area in a material, which can affect its mechanical and electronic properties."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000595> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000596> (deformation)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000596> "deformation"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000596> "The deformation is a process describing a change in the shape, size, or structure of a material under the influence of stress or force."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000596> obo:BFO_0000015)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000597> (density)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000597> "density"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000597> "The density is a universal intensive quality representing the unit mass of a portion of matter per unit volume."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000597> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> (device)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> "Gerät"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> "device"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> "A physical or virtual entity used to perform a specific function or task, often involving measurement, manipulation, or analysis of materials."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> "Ein physisches oder virtuelles Objekt, das verwendet wird, um eine bestimmte Funktion oder Aufgabe auszuführen, häufig im Zusammenhang mit der Messung, Manipulation oder Analyse von Materialien."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> obo:BFO_0000030)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000618> (elastic modulus)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000618> "elastic modulus"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000618> "An elastic modulus is a measure of a material's stiffness, defined as the ratio of stress to strain in the elastic deformation region."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000618> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000949>)
