# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> (temperature)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> "The concept refers to an absolute tempeature, not to be mistaken with temperature difference."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> "To express that an object has a temperature, the property 'intensive bearer of' can be used. It implies a chain of: object consists of some portion of matter and portion of matter bearer of some temperature."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> "temperature"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> "The temperature is a fundamental intensive quality representing the average atomic or molcular movement or vibration of a portion of matter."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000981> (thermal property)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000981> "thermal property"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000981> "A thermal property is a material property representing attributes of a material that describe its behavior under temperature changes, such as thermal conductivity and expansion."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000981> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000981> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:BFO_0000054 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000520>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001008> (waver irradiation)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001008> "waver irradiation"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001008> "A waver irradiation is an irradiation describing an exposure of a material or system to electromagnetic waves or radiation."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001008> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000802>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020001> (filler role)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020001> "filler role"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020001> "Filler is the role of a PortionOfDisconnectedMatter that implies being hosted in a Matrix."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020001> obo:BFO_0000023)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020003> (crystal)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020003> "crystal"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020003> "A crystal is an object that has part some entities that concretize a Bravais lattice."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020003> obo:BFO_0000030)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020005> (porosity)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020005> "porosity"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020005> "The porosity is a quality describing the fraction of the materials (enclosing) spatial region occupied by pores."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020005> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020023> (metallic grain structures)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020023> "metallic grain structures"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020023> "The metallic grain structures is a categorical value specification that specifies value of the  metallic grain structure quality. It describes the morphology of polycrystalline metallic materials. Polycrystalline metallic materials will typically form their grain structures as one of those categories or a transition or mixture state of those."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020023> ObjectOneOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020027> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020097> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020100> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020107> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020109> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020110> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020111>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020023> obo:OBI_0001930)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> (bravais lattice (3d))

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> "TODO: possibly extend for 2D (Graphene etc)

More elaborate crystal descriptions may be found in http://emmo.info/domain-crystallography/crystallography or https://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/disos/cso"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> "bravais lattice (3d)"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> "The Bravais lattice is a categorical value specification that specifies value of the crystal structure quality. It describes the possible geometric arrangement of lattice points in a crystal. The present descriptor is limited to the 14 possible three-dimensional arrangements."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> ObjectOneOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020007> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020008> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020009> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020010> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020011> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020012> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020013> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020014> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020015> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020016> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020017> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020018> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020019>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> obo:OBI_0001930)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> (proportion)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> "proportion"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> "concentration"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> "fraction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> "A Proportion is a relational quality between two entites (the whole and the part) which quantifies the relation between the whole and its part."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> obo:BFO_0000145)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020102> (mass proportion)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020102> "mass proportion"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020102> "The Mass Proportion is a Proportion which quantifies the mass of the part relative to the mass of the whole."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020102> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> (molar proportion)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> "molar proportion"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> "Molar Ratio"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> "The Molar Proportion is the proportion which quantifies the entities count of the part in relation to the entites count of the whole."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> "The molar ratio of hydrogen gas H2 molecules to water H2O molecules is 1/1 in the oxyhydrogen reaction. The molar ratio of oxigen molecules O2 to water molecules is 2/1.
The molar ratio of carbon dioxide to average atmosphere air is 420 ppm as of 2022 AD."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020104> (volume proportion)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020104> "volume proportion"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020104> "The Mass Proportion is a Proportion which quantifies the volume of the part relative to the volume of the whole."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020104> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> (polycrystal)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> "polycrystal"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> "Polycrystalline structure"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> "Polycrystal is a connected object aggregate that has continuant part some crystal grains"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:BFO_0000051 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000663>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> (grain size distribution)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> "grain size distribution"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> "An intensive quality describing the lower length scale object aggregate (grains) that is part of the material."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116> (aggregate state value)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116> "aggregate state value"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116> "The aggregate state value is a categorical value specification that specifies value of the aggregatge state quality."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116> ObjectOneOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020117> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020118> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020120> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020121> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020122> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020123> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020124> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020125>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116> obo:OBI_0001930)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> (intensive quality)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> "intensive quality"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> "Point property"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> "An intensive quality is a qualty that inheres in only portion of matter and thus is independent of the bearers (system-) size."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> obo:BFO_0000019)
DisjointClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132> (size)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132> "size"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132> "Size is the quality of a material entity that describes its spatial extend."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143> (process chain)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143> "process chain"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143> "A process chain is a process that 'has contiuant part' subprocesses S1...Sn where S1...Sn precede each other and where some object or object aggregate that are output of Sn are then input to Sn+1."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143> obo:BFO_0000015)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> (extensive quality)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> "extensive quality"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> "An extensive quality is a qualty that inheres in only object or object aggregate or fiat object part or chemical entity and is dependent on the bearers (system-) size."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> obo:BFO_0000019)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> (composition)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> "composition"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> "Composition is a morphological quality describing the types and proportions of compounds (but not chemical elements) present in a portion of matter."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> "4 vol.% nitric acid solution, Styrene-Butadiene-Styrene (SBS) Block Copolymer with 50 vol.% of both styrene and butadiene"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> (metallic grain structure)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> "metallic grain structure"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> "metallic grain structure characterizes the distinct phases in the microscopic structure of a metallic material. It concretizes ferrite, austenite, martensite, etc."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> ObjectExactCardinality(1 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020023>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020023>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> (length)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "Length is a size that describes the spacial extend of its bearer in one dimension."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "length"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "dimension"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "Length is a one dimensional size.")
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050004> (thermoplastics)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050004> "thermoplastics"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050004> "A Thermoplastic is a Polymer that becomes moldable when heated and solidifies upon cooling."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050004> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000888>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0200002> (Spritzgießen)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/source> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0200002> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8580, group 1.2.2 “Spritzgießen”."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/source> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0200002> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN 8580, Gruppe 1.2.2 „Spritzgießen“."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0200002> "Spritzgießen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0200002> "injection molding"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0200002> "injection moulding; plastic injection molding"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0200002> "A primary shaping process in which plastic granules are plasticised in an injection unit and the melt is injected under high pressure into a closed mold cavity, where it cools and solidifies to the final part shape."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0200002> "Urformverfahren, bei dem Kunststoffgranulat in einem Plastifizieraggregat aufgeschmolzen und die Schmelze mit hohem Druck in einen geschlossenen Formhohlraum eingespritzt wird, wo sie verdichtet, abkühlt und zum Formteil erstarrt."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0200002> "Injection molding of polypropylene housings."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0200002> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000907>)


